description:
&lt;p&gt;There are 2 substantive band 6 vacancies available within Centenary Theatres Castle Hill Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;X1 wte theatre band 6, to be appointed to an internal band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;X1 wte recovery band 6, applications welcomed from internal and external applicants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would like to invite applications from practitioners who have at least 2 years experience as a band 5 or above, to work in these busy, exciting and expanding areas. Experience in theatres and recovery is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require highly motivated, hardworking individuals, working as a highly skilled member of the multidisciplinary team. The successful applicants must possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills to join a strong proactive management team. The ability to adapt well to change, participate in theatre/recovery audits and work well as part of a well, established team is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service currently covers Monday to Friday at present. Staff will be expected to participate in the 24hour, 7 days a week on call rota-covering emergencies out of hours. Further developments may increase the need for weekend or unsocial work in the future, so a flexible attitude to meet the needs of the service is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful we can offer a Personal Development Plan closely supported by the Charge ODP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nicola Anson, Charge Operating Department Practitioner nicola.anson@hey.nhs.uk 01428 468398&lt;/p&gt;
